description: Former President Donald Trump and Vice President Harris are taking on vastly different approaches to their campaigns as Election Day nears. And, California could determine who controls the House.
title: The 2 paths deciding the presidency. And, California could determine House control

description: Their wages have always been low. With rising inflation and falling prices paid by Western companies for clothing, they're protesting for better pay — and hoping the new government will spur change.
title: Why the garment workers of Bangladesh are feeling poorer than ever

description: Striking machinists at Boeing vote Wednesday on a new contract offer. Even before the strike, the company was grappling with production and quality control problems that led to billions in losses.
title: Boeing workers vote on a new contract, but the company’s problems are far from over

description: Malcolm Campbell remembers Don Lawson, the high school civics teacher who helped him understand the true value of education.
title: 'A light went off in my head': A professor honors his high school civics teacher

description: Vice President Harris is banking on the support of young voters. But new polling shows potential roadblocks for Harris in replicating the historically high youth support President Biden received in 2020.
title: Harris needs young voters of color to win. A new poll finds cracks in her support

description: With seven states up for grabs, here are the likely scenarios that would put either candidate in the White House.
title: These are the 2 paths either Trump or Harris has to follow to become president

description: A new Biden administration effort to raise Head Start teacher wages could force the federally funded preschool program to serve fewer children.
title: These teachers often live in poverty. A pay raise could help — but there’s a cost

description: Braddock, Pennsylvania lost most of its population over the past almost 100 years, due largely to U.S. Steel's decline. Here's how some locals feel about the company's potential sale to the Japanese.
title: U.S. Steel’s decline nearly killed this town. Its sale could save it

description: Canada's deputy prime minister said she believes Justin Trudeau has the support of a majority of Liberals in Parliament as some prepare to confront him Wednesday in the hopes of convincing him to step down.
title: Canadian Cabinet voices support for Trudeau as some Liberals prepare to confront him

description: Egypt has been fighting malaria for nearly 100 years. WHO declares a country malaria-free when the disease has not been present for at least three consecutive years before the designation.
title: Egypt has been declared malaria-free by the World Health Organization

description: Denny’s says it’s closing 150 of its lowest-performing restaurants in an effort to turn around the brand’s flagging sales. About half of the closures will happen this year and the rest in 2025.
title: Denny's says it expects to close 150 locations by the end of 2025
